HEADWORD: Abator
<hw>A*ba"tor</hw> <pr>(⟦adot⟧*b⟦amac⟧t"⟦etil⟧r)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<fld>(Law)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>One who abates a nuisance.</def>
<sd>(b)</sd> <def>A person who, without right, enters into a freehold on
the death of the last possessor, before the heir or devisee.</def>
<rj><au>Blackstone.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

